INSERT INTO `myapp_recipe` VALUES (1,'Veg Chowmein','Veg Chow Mein is a popular Indo-Chinese dish featuring stir-fried noodles and mixed vegetables. It\'s prepared by boiling noodles, stir-frying a variety of vegetables with ginger and garlic, then tossing everything together with a savory sauce made from soy sauce and vinegar. The dish is versatile, customizable, and perfect for a quick and flavorful meal during any occasion.','200g chow mein noodles\r\n2 tablespoons vegetable oil\r\n2 cloves garlic, minced\r\n1 small onion, thinly sliced\r\n1 bell pepper, thinly sliced\r\n1 carrot, julienned\r\n1 cup cabbage, shredded\r\n1 cup bean sprouts\r\n2 tablespoons soy sauce\r\n1 tablespoon oyster sauce\r\n1 teaspoon sesame oil\r\nSalt and pepper to taste\r\nOptional: chopped green onions, for garnish','Cook the chow mein noodles according to the package instructions. Drain and set aside.\r\nHeat vegetable oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.\r\nAdd minced garlic and sliced onion to the skillet. Stir-fry for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.\r\nAdd the sliced bell pepper, julienned carrot, shredded cabbage, and bean sprouts to the skillet. Stir-fry for another 3-4 minutes until the vegetables are tender-crisp.\r\nAdd the cooked chow mein noodles to the skillet.\r\nPour soy sauce, oyster sauce, and sesame oil over the noodles and vegetables. Toss everything together until well combined.\r\nSeason with salt and pepper to taste. Stir-fry for another 2-3 minutes to heat everything through.\r\nRemove from heat and transfer to serving plates.\r\nGarnish with chopped green onions if desired.\r\nServe hot and enjoy your delicious vegetable chow mein!','2024-05-15 02:18:46.177442',8,13,'recipe_images/chaumin.jpg'),(2,'Chicken Biriyani','Chicken Biryani is a classic Indian rice dish known for its rich flavors, aromatic spices, and tender chicken pieces. This traditional dish is a beloved favorite at special occasions and gatherings, showcasing the culinary expertise and cultural heritage of Indian cuisine.','For Marinating Chicken:\r\n500 grams chicken, cut into pieces\r\n1 cup plain yogurt\r\n2 tablespoons ginger-garlic paste\r\n1 teaspoon red chili powder\r\n1 teaspoon turmeric powder\r\n1 teaspoon garam masala powder\r\nSalt to taste\r\nFor Rice:\r\n2 cups Basmati rice, soaked for 30 minutes and drained\r\nWater for boiling rice\r\nSalt to taste\r\nWhole spices (2 bay leaves, 4-5 cloves, 4-5 green cardamom pods, 2-inch cinnamon stick)\r\nOther Ingredients:\r\n2 large onions, thinly sliced\r\n2 tomatoes, chopped\r\n2 green chilies, slit lengthwise\r\n1/4 cup chopped fresh coriander leaves (cilantro)\r\n1/4 cup chopped fresh mint leaves\r\n1/4 cup fried onions (optional, for garnish)\r\n1/4 cup ghee or vegetable oil\r\nSaffron strands soaked in warm milk (for garnish, optional)','Marinate the Chicken:\r\nIn a large bowl, combine the chicken pieces with yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric powder, garam masala powder, and salt. Mix well to coat the chicken evenly. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight for best results.\r\nPrepare the Rice:\r\nIn a large pot, bring water to a boil. Add salt and whole spices (bay leaves, cloves, cardamom, cinnamon).\r\nAdd the soaked and drained Basmati rice to the boiling water. Cook until the rice is 70% cooked (parboiled). Drain the rice and set aside.\r\nCook the Chicken Masala:\r\nIn a large, heavy-bottomed pot or Dutch oven, heat ghee or oil over medium heat.\r\nAdd the sliced onions and sauté until golden brown.\r\nAdd chopped tomatoes and green chilies. Cook until the tomatoes are soft and oil starts to separate.\r\nAdd marinated chicken pieces along with the marinade. Cook for 8-10 minutes until the chicken is partially cooked and the masala is well-coated.\r\nLayering the Biryani:\r\nIn the same pot, spread half of the partially cooked rice over the chicken masala in an even layer.\r\nSprinkle chopped coriander leaves and mint leaves over the rice.\r\nLayer the remaining rice on top.\r\nGarnish with fried onions and drizzle saffron-infused milk over the rice for added flavor and color.\r\nDum Cooking (Steam Cooking):\r\nCover the pot with a tight-fitting lid or seal it with aluminum foil to trap the steam.\r\nReduce the heat to low and cook the biryani on dum for 20-25 minutes until the chicken is fully cooked and the rice is tender.\r\nRemove from heat and let the biryani rest for 5-10 minutes before serving.\r\nServe:\r\nGently fluff the biryani with a fork to mix the layers.\r\nServe hot with raita (yogurt dip) or salad on the side.','2024-05-15 02:19:06.719958',9,15,'media/recipe_images/chicken_biriyani_4S8zA29.webp'),(3,'Veg Pulao','Veg Pulao is a delicious and aromatic rice dish that showcases a medley of vegetables cooked with fragrant spices and Basmati rice. It\'s a quick and easy one-pot meal that offers a balance of flavors and textures, making it a popular choice for both everyday meals and special occasions. Veg Pulao is versatile and can be customized with various vegetables, herbs, and spices, allowing for endless variations to suit individual tastes.','Basmati Rice: Long-grain rice known for its fragrant aroma and delicate texture.\r\nMixed Vegetables:\r\nCarrots\r\nGreen peas\r\nGreen beans\r\nCauliflower florets\r\nPotatoes\r\nBell peppers (capsicum)\r\nOnions.\r\nAromatics and Spices:\r\nWhole spices (such as cumin seeds, cinnamon, cloves, cardamom)\r\nGinger\r\nGarlic\r\nGreen chilies (optional, for heat)\r\nTurmeric powder\r\nCumin powder\r\nCoriander powder.\r\nFresh Herbs:\r\nFresh coriander leaves (cilantro), chopped.\r\nFresh mint leaves, chopped (optional).\r\nGhee or Vegetable Oil: For cooking the pulao and enhancing flavor.\r\nSalt: To season the dish.\r\nWater or Vegetable Broth: For cooking the rice and vegetables.','Prepare the Rice:\r\nWash the Basmati rice under running water until the water runs clear. Soak the rice in water for about 30 minutes, then drain well.\r\nSauté Aromatics and Whole Spices:\r\nHeat ghee or oil in a large pot or pressure cooker over medium heat.\r\nAdd whole spices like cumin seeds, cinnamon, cloves, and cardamom. Sauté until they release their aroma.\r\nAdd Aromatics:\r\nAdd finely chopped ginger, garlic, and green chilies to the pot. Sauté for a minute until fragrant.\r\nAdd Vegetables:\r\nAdd chopped onions and sauté until they turn translucent.\r\nAdd diced vegetables like carrots, peas, green beans, cauliflower, and potatoes. Sauté for a few minutes until they are slightly tender.\r\nAdd Spices:\r\nSprinkle turmeric powder, cumin powder, and coriander powder over the vegetables. Mix well to coat the vegetables evenly with the spices.\r\nCook Rice:\r\nAdd the drained Basmati rice to the pot. Stir gently to combine with the vegetables and spices.\r\nPour in the measured water or vegetable broth. Season with salt to taste.\r\nCooking Methods:\r\nFor stovetop method: Cover the pot with a tight-fitting lid and cook on low heat until the rice is tender and the water is absorbed, about 15-20 minutes. Fluff the rice with a fork before serving.\r\nFor pressure cooker method: Close the pressure cooker lid and cook on medium heat for 1 whistle. Then, reduce the heat to low and cook for another 5 minutes. Allow the pressure to release naturally before opening the lid.\r\nGarnish and Serve:\r\nOnce the rice is cooked, remove the pot from heat.\r\nGarnish the Veg Pulao with freshly chopped coriander leaves and mint leaves for added freshness and flavor.\r\nServe hot as a standalone dish or as a side with yogurt, raita, or any curry of your choice.','2024-05-15 02:19:16.054296',8,1,'media/recipe_images/veg_pulao.jpg'),(4,'Non-veg fried rice','Non-veg fried rice is a flavorful and satisfying dish made with cooked white rice, boneless chicken, shrimp, mixed vegetables, and a savory combination of soy sauce, oyster sauce, and sesame oil. This quick and easy recipe involves stir-frying the ingredients together in a skillet or wok until they are well combined and heated through. It\'s a versatile dish that can be customized with your favorite vegetables and protein choices. Enjoy this delicious Non-veg Fried Rice as a main course for lunch or dinner!','2 cups of cooked white rice\r\n200 grams of boneless chicken, cut into small pieces\r\n100 grams of shrimp, peeled and deveined\r\n2 eggs, beaten\r\n1 cup of mixed vegetables (carrots, peas, bell peppers, etc.)\r\n3 cloves of garlic, minced\r\n2 tablespoons of soy sauce\r\n1 tablespoon of oyster sauce\r\n1 tablespoon of sesame oil\r\n2 tablespoons of vegetable oil\r\nSalt and pepper to taste\r\nGreen onions for garnish','Heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add the beaten eggs and scramble them until cooked through. Remove from the skillet and set aside.\r\nIn the same skillet, add another tablespoon of vegetable oil. Add the minced garlic and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds.\r\nAdd the chicken pieces to the skillet and cook until they are no longer pink, about 5-7 minutes.\r\nAdd the shrimp to the skillet and cook until they turn pink, about 2-3 minutes.\r\nStir in the mixed vegetables and cooked rice. Cook for an additional 3-4 minutes, stirring constantly.\r\nAdd the soy sauce, oyster sauce, and sesame oil to the skillet. Stir well to combine and coat the rice evenly with the sauces.\r\nReturn the scrambled eggs to the skillet and stir to incorporate them into the rice mixture.\r\nSeason with salt and pepper to taste. Cook for another 2-3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until everything is heated through.\r\nGarnish with chopped green onions before serving.\r\nServe hot and enjoy your delicious Non-veg Fried Rice!','2024-05-15 02:19:22.735388',9,1,'recipe_images/non_veg_friedrice.jpg'),(5,'Chicken Butter Masala','Chicken Butter Masala is a classic North Indian dish featuring tender chicken cooked in a rich, creamy tomato-based sauce. It\'s known for its indulgent flavor profile, combining aromatic spices with the richness of butter and cream.','500 grams boneless chicken, cut into bite-sized pieces\r\n2 onions, finely chopped\r\n2 tomatoes, pureed\r\n2 tablespoons butter\r\n2 tablespoons oil\r\n1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\r\n1 teaspoon red chili powder\r\n1 teaspoon coriander powder\r\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\r\n1 teaspoon garam masala\r\n1/2 cup fresh cream\r\nSalt to taste\r\nFresh coriander leaves for garnishing\r\nFor Marinade:\r\n1/2 cup yogurt\r\n1 tablespoon lemon juice\r\n1 teaspoon red chili powder\r\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\r\nSalt to taste','In a bowl, mix yogurt, lemon juice, red chili powder, turmeric powder, and salt. Add chicken pieces to the marinade, coat well, and let it marinate for at least 30 minutes.\r\nHeat oil in a pan over medium heat. Add marinated chicken pieces and cook until they are golden brown and cooked through. Remove the chicken from the pan and set aside.\r\nIn the same pan, add butter. Once melted, add chopped onions and sauté until they turn translucent.\r\nAdd ginger-garlic paste and sauté for another couple of minutes until the raw smell disappears.\r\nAdd pureed tomatoes and cook until the oil starts to separate from the masala.\r\nAdd red chili powder, coriander powder, turmeric powder, garam masala, and salt. Mix well and cook for a few minutes.\r\nAdd the cooked chicken to the tomato mixture and mix until well combined.\r\nPour in fresh cream and stir until the sauce is creamy and well blended.\r\nCook for a few more minutes until the chicken is coated with the sauce and heated through.\r\nGarnish with fresh coriander leaves and serve hot with naan, roti, or rice.','2024-05-15 02:26:31.536830',9,13,'recipe_images/chicken_butter_masala.webp'),(6,'Veg Biriyani','Veg Biryani is a flavorful and aromatic rice dish made with mixed vegetables, fragrant basmati rice, and a blend of spices. It\'s a popular vegetarian version of the traditional biryani, cooked with layers of vegetables and rice, infused with saffron, and garnished with fried onions, nuts, and raisins. This dish is perfect for special occasions or as a hearty meal any day of the week.','2 cups basmati rice\r\n1 large onion, thinly sliced\r\n1 cup mixed vegetables (carrots, peas, potatoes, beans, cauliflower, etc.)\r\n1/2 cup yogurt\r\n2 tomatoes, chopped\r\n2 green chilies, slit lengthwise\r\n2 tablespoons ginger-garlic paste\r\n1 teaspoon cumin seeds\r\n4-5 whole cloves\r\n2-3 green cardamom pods\r\n1-inch cinnamon stick\r\n1 bay leaf\r\n1/4 teaspoon turmeric powder\r\n1/2 teaspoon red chili powder\r\n1/2 teaspoon garam masala powder\r\nA pinch of saffron strands (optional)\r\n1/4 cup milk\r\n2 tablespoons ghee (clarified butter) or oil\r\nSalt to taste\r\nFresh coriander leaves for garnishing\r\nFried onions, nuts, and raisins for garnishing (optional)','Wash the basmati rice in cold water until the water runs clear. Soak the rice in water for 30 minutes, then drain and set aside.\r\nIn a small bowl, soak the saffron strands in warm milk and set aside.\r\nHeat ghee or oil in a large pan or pressure cooker over medium heat. Add the cumin seeds, cloves, cardamom pods, cinnamon stick, and bay leaf. Sauté for a minute until fragrant.\r\nAdd the thinly sliced onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.\r\nAdd the ginger-garlic paste and green chilies. Sauté for another minute.\r\nAdd the chopped tomatoes and cook until they turn soft and mushy.\r\nAdd the mixed vegetables and cook for a few minutes until they are slightly tender.\r\nAdd the turmeric powder, red chili powder, and garam masala powder. Mix well to combine.\r\nAdd the soaked and drained basmati rice to the pan. Gently stir to mix the rice with the vegetables and spices.\r\nAdd the beaten yogurt and saffron-infused milk to the pan. Mix gently to combine all the ingredients.\r\nPour in enough water to cover the rice by about 1 inch. Season with salt according to your taste.\r\nCover the pan with a tight-fitting lid and cook on low heat until the rice is cooked through and fluffy, and the vegetables are tender. If using a pressure cooker, cook for about 1-2 whistles.\r\nOnce done, remove the pan from heat and let it sit, covered, for 5-10 minutes.\r\nFluff the Veg Biryani gently with a fork. Garnish with fresh coriander leaves and fried onions, nuts, and raisins if desired.\r\nServe hot with raita (yogurt dip) or your favorite side dish.','2024-05-15 02:19:35.335939',8,1,'recipe_images/veg_biriyani_B5qWFG8.webp'),(7,'Mutton Biriyani','Mutton biryani is a classic Indian dish consisting of fragrant basmati rice layered with succulent pieces of mutton, aromatic spices, caramelized onions, and fresh herbs. Slow-cooked to perfection, this rich and flavorful dish is a favorite at festive occasions and gatherings.','500 grams mutton, cut into pieces\r\n2 cups basmati rice, soaked for 30 minutes\r\n3 onions, thinly sliced\r\n2 tomatoes, chopped\r\n1/2 cup yogurt\r\n1/4 cup chopped coriander leaves\r\n1/4 cup chopped mint leaves\r\n2 green chilies, slit\r\n2 tablespoons ginger-garlic paste\r\n1 tablespoon red chili powder\r\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\r\n1 teaspoon garam masala powder\r\n1/2 teaspoon cumin seeds\r\n4 cloves\r\n2-inch cinnamon stick\r\n2-3 green cardamom pods\r\n1 bay leaf\r\n1/4 cup ghee\r\nSalt to taste\r\nSaffron strands (optional)\r\nFried onions for garnish\r\nChopped coriander leaves for garnish\r\nLemon wedges for serving','Heat ghee in a large pan or pressure cooker. Add cumin seeds, cloves, cinnamon stick, green cardamom pods, and bay leaf. Sauté for a minute until fragrant.\r\nAdd sliced onions and sauté until golden brown.\r\nAdd ginger-garlic paste and slit green chilies. Sauté for a couple of minutes.\r\nAdd chopped tomatoes and cook until they turn mushy.\r\nAdd mutton pieces, red chili powder, turmeric powder, and salt. Mix well and cook for 5-6 minutes.\r\nAdd yogurt, chopped coriander leaves, and mint leaves. Mix well and cook for another 5 minutes.\r\nAdd soaked basmati rice and mix gently without breaking the rice grains.\r\nAdd water (the ratio of rice to water is usually 1:2 for biryani). If using a pressure cooker, cover and cook for 1 whistle on medium heat. If using a pan, cover and cook on low heat until the rice is cooked and the mutton is tender.\r\nOnce cooked, let the biryani rest for a few minutes. Then fluff it up gently with a fork.\r\nGarnish with fried onions, chopped coriander leaves, and saffron strands (if using).\r\nServe hot with lemon wedges and raita.','2024-05-15 02:18:13.313422',9,15,'media/recipe_images/mutton_biriyani.jpg'),(8,'Veg Manchurian','Veg Manchurian is a popular Indo-Chinese dish made with mixed vegetables, formed into balls, and deep-fried until golden brown. These crispy veggie balls are then tossed in a flavorful Manchurian sauce, creating a delightful combination of sweet, sour, and spicy flavors. It\'s a perfect appetizer or side dish for any Asian-inspired meal, and it\'s loved by vegetarians and non-vegetarians alike.','1 cup finely chopped mixed vegetables (cabbage, carrots, capsicum, beans)\r\n1/2 cup finely chopped cabbage\r\n1/4 cup all-purpose flour\r\n1/4 cup cornflour\r\n1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\r\n1 tablespoon soy sauce\r\n1/2 teaspoon black pepper powder\r\nSalt to taste\r\nOil for deep frying\r\n2 tablespoons oil\r\n1 tablespoon finely chopped garlic\r\n1 tablespoon finely chopped ginger\r\n1/4 cup finely chopped spring onions (whites)\r\n1/4 cup finely chopped capsicum\r\n1 tablespoon soy sauce\r\n1 tablespoon tomato ketchup\r\n1 tablespoon chili sauce\r\n1 tablespoon vinegar\r\n1/2 teaspoon black pepper powder\r\n1/2 teaspoon sugar\r\nSalt to taste\r\n2 cups water\r\n1 tablespoon cornflour mixed with 2 tablespoons water (for slurry)','In a mixing bowl, combine chopped mixed vegetables, cabbage, all-purpose flour, cornflour, ginger-garlic paste, soy sauce, black pepper powder, and salt.\r\nMix everything well to form a sticky dough.\r\nDivide the mixture into small portions and shape them into round balls.\r\nHeat oil in a deep frying pan over medium heat. Once the oil is hot, add the veggie balls in batches and fry until they turn golden brown and crispy. Remove them from the oil and drain excess oil on paper towels.\r\nHeat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pan over medium heat.\r\nAdd finely chopped garlic and ginger. Saute for a minute until fragrant.\r\nAdd finely chopped spring onions (whites) and capsicum. Stir-fry for 2-3 minutes.\r\nNow, add soy sauce, tomato ketchup, chili sauce, vinegar, black pepper powder, sugar, and salt. Mix well.\r\nPour 2 cups of water into the pan and bring the mixture to a boil.\r\nOnce the sauce starts boiling, add the cornflour slurry gradually while stirring continuously to avoid lumps.\r\nCook the sauce for another 2-3 minutes until it thickens to the desired consistency.\r\nAdd the fried veggie balls to the sauce and toss gently until they are well coated with the sauce.\r\nGarnish with chopped spring onion greens and serve hot.\r\nVeg Manchurian is best enjoyed with fried rice or noodles.','2024-05-15 03:17:47.532024',8,14,'media/recipe_images/veg_machurian.webp'),(9,'Palak Paneer','Palak Paneer is a popular Indian dish made with spinach (palak) and paneer (cottage cheese) cooked in a flavorful gravy. It\'s a nutritious and delicious vegetarian option, packed with the goodness of spinach and protein-rich paneer.','250 grams Paneer (cottage cheese), cubed\r\n300 grams Spinach (palak), washed and finely chopped\r\n1 large Onion, finely chopped\r\n2 Tomatoes, finely chopped\r\n4 Garlic cloves, minced\r\n1 inch Ginger, grated\r\n2 Green chilies, finely chopped\r\n1 teaspoon Cumin seeds\r\n1/2 teaspoon Turmeric powder\r\n1 teaspoon Red chili powder\r\n1 teaspoon Coriander powder\r\n1/2 teaspoon Garam masala\r\nSalt, to taste\r\n2 tablespoons Oil or ghee\r\n2 tablespoons Fresh cream (optional)\r\n1 tablespoon Kasuri methi (dried fenugreek leaves), crushed (optional)','Heat 2 tablespoons of oil or ghee in a pan and add 1 teaspoon of cumin seeds. Let them splutter.\r\nAdd 4 minced garlic cloves, 1 inch grated ginger, and 2 chopped green chilies. Saute until fragrant.\r\nAdd 1 large finely chopped onion and cook until translucent.\r\nNow, add 2 finely chopped tomatoes and cook until they turn soft and mushy.\r\nAdd 1/2 teaspoon of turmeric powder, 1 teaspoon of red chili powder, 1 teaspoon of coriander powder, and salt to taste. Mix well.\r\nAdd 300 grams of finely chopped spinach (palak) and cook until it wilts down and becomes soft.\r\nAllow the mixture to cool down a bit, then blend it into a smooth puree using a blender or food processor.\r\nReturn the pureed mixture to the pan and bring it to a simmer.\r\nAdd 250 grams of cubed paneer (cottage cheese) and 1/2 teaspoon of garam masala. Mix gently to coat the paneer with the spinach gravy.\r\nLet it simmer for a few minutes until the paneer absorbs the flavors of the gravy.\r\nOptionally, add 2 tablespoons of fresh cream for a creamy texture and richness.\r\nSprinkle 1 tablespoon of crushed kasuri methi (dried fenugreek leaves) on top for added flavor (optional).\r\nServe hot with roti, naan, or rice. Enjoy your delicious Palak Paneer!','2024-05-15 02:18:00.228654',8,1,'media/recipe_images/palak_paneer.jpg'),(10,'Pav Bhaji','Pav Bhaji is a popular street food dish from India, especially Mumbai. It consists of a spicy and flavorful vegetable mash served with buttered and toasted dinner rolls (pav). The bhaji, or vegetable mash, is made from a combination of boiled potatoes, cauliflower, green peas, onions, tomatoes, and bell peppers cooked with a blend of aromatic spices like pav bhaji masala, red chili powder, and turmeric. It\'s typically garnished with fresh coriander leaves and served with lemon wedges for a tangy kick. Pav Bhaji is loved for its bold flavors, creamy texture, and comforting warmth, making it a favorite snack or meal option for many.','4 medium potatoes, boiled and mashed\r\n1 cup cauliflower florets, boiled and mashed\r\n1 cup green peas, boiled\r\n2 large onions, finely chopped\r\n2 large tomatoes, finely chopped\r\n1 green bell pepper, finely chopped\r\n2 tablespoons pav bhaji masala\r\n1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\r\n1 teaspoon red chili powder\r\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder\r\nSalt to taste\r\nButter for cooking\r\nPav (dinner rolls) for serving\r\nFresh coriander leaves for garnish\r\nLemon wedges for serving','Heat butter in a pan and add chopped onions. Saute until translucent.\r\nAdd ginger-garlic paste and saute until the raw smell disappears.\r\nAdd chopped tomatoes and cook until they turn mushy.\r\nAdd chopped bell pepper and cook for a couple of minutes.\r\nAdd pav bhaji masala, red chili powder, turmeric powder, and salt. Mix well.\r\nAdd mashed potatoes, cauliflower, and boiled green peas. Mix thoroughly.\r\nMash the mixture using a potato masher or back of a spoon until well combined.\r\nCook the bhaji on low heat for 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally.\r\nToast the pav (dinner rolls) on a hot griddle with butter until golden brown.\r\nGarnish the bhaji with chopped coriander leaves and serve hot with toasted pav, lemon wedges, and extra butter on top.','2024-05-15 02:17:50.084029',8,1,'media/recipe_images/pav_bhaji.jpg'),(11,'Peri peri prawns','Peri peri prawns are succulent and flavorful seafood delights, perfect for those who enjoy a spicy kick with their meal. Marinated in a zesty peri peri sauce with garlic, lemon juice, and olive oil, these prawns are grilled to perfection, resulting in a smoky and aromatic dish. Served hot and garnished with fresh parsley, peri peri prawns make for a delightful appetizer or main course, guaranteed to satisfy your taste buds with every bite.','500g large prawns, peeled and deveined\r\n2 tablespoons peri peri sauce\r\n2 cloves garlic, minced\r\n1 tablespoon lemon juice\r\n2 tablespoons olive oil\r\nSalt and pepper to taste\r\nChopped fresh parsley for garnish','In a bowl, combine the peri peri sauce, minced garlic, lemon juice, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Mix well to combine.\r\nAdd the peeled and deveined prawns to the bowl and toss them in the marinade until they are well coated. Cover the bowl and let the prawns marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours for maximum flavor.\r\nHeat a grill or grill pan over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the marinated prawns to the grill and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until they are cooked through and have grill marks.\r\nOnce cooked, remove the prawns from the grill and transfer them to a serving plate. Garnish with chopped fresh parsley.\r\nServe the peri peri prawns hot with your favorite side dishes, such as rice, salad, or crusty bread.','2024-05-15 02:17:06.112787',9,1,'media/recipe_images/peri-peri-prewn.webp'),(12,'Mutton ghee roast','Mutton ghee roast is a popular South Indian dish known for its rich, spicy, and aromatic flavors. It features tender mutton pieces marinated and cooked in a luscious blend of ghee (clarified butter) and an array of aromatic spices. This dish is often enjoyed as a main course and pairs well with steamed rice, roti, or naan.','500 grams mutton, cleaned and cut into pieces\r\n3 tablespoons ghee (clarified butter)\r\n2 onions, finely chopped\r\n2 tomatoes, finely chopped\r\n1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\r\n1 tablespoon red chili powder\r\n1 teaspoon turmeric powder\r\n2 teaspoons coriander powder\r\n1 teaspoon cumin powder\r\nSalt to taste\r\nFresh coriander leaves for garnish\r\n6-8 dried red chilies\r\n1 teaspoon peppercorns\r\n1 teaspoon cumin seeds\r\n1 teaspoon fenugreek seeds\r\n6-8 cloves garlic\r\n1-inch ginger piece\r\n1 tablespoon tamarind paste\r\n2 tablespoons ghee','Dry roast the ingredients for the masala until fragrant and grind them into a fine paste with a little water.\r\nHeat ghee in a pan and sauté onions until golden brown.\r\nAdd ginger-garlic paste and cook until the raw smell disappears.\r\nAdd chopped tomatoes and cook until they turn mushy.\r\nAdd the ground masala paste, red chili powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, cumin powder, and salt. Cook until the ghee starts to separate.\r\nAdd the mutton pieces and mix well to coat them with the masala.\r\nAdd water as needed, cover, and cook until the mutton is tender and the gravy thickens.\r\nGarnish with fresh coriander leaves and serve hot with rice or roti.','2024-05-15 02:33:08.082504',9,13,'media/recipe_images/mutton-ghee-roast.webp'),(16,'Paneer Butter Masala','Paneer Butter Masala Recipe is one of India’s most popular paneer preparation. This restaurant style recipe with soft paneer cubes dunked in a creamy, lightly spiced tomato sauce or gravy is a best one that I have been making for a long time. This rich dish is best served with roti or chapati, paratha, naan or rumali roti.','200 grams paneer (cottage cheese), cut into cubes\r\n2 tablespoons butter\r\n2 tablespoons oil\r\n1 large onion, finely chopped\r\n2 tomatoes, pureed\r\n1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\r\n1 teaspoon red chili powder\r\n1 teaspoon turmeric powder\r\n1 teaspoon coriander powder\r\n1 teaspoon garam masala\r\n1 teaspoon kasuri methi (dried fenugreek leaves)\r\nSalt to taste\r\n1/2 cup fresh cream\r\nCoriander leaves for garnishing','Heat oil and butter in a pan over medium heat.\r\nAdd chopped onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.\r\nAdd ginger-garlic paste and sauté for a minute until the raw smell disappears.\r\nAdd pureed tomatoes and cook until the oil starts to separate from the masala.\r\nAdd red chili powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, garam masala, and salt. Mix well and cook for 2-3 minutes.\r\nAdd paneer cubes and mix gently, ensuring the paneer is coated well with the masala.\r\nCrush kasuri methi between your palms and sprinkle it over the paneer masala.\r\nPour fresh cream into the pan and stir well. Cook for another 2-3 minutes.\r\nGarnish with chopped coriander leaves.\r\nServe hot with naan, roti, or rice.','2024-05-15 02:13:10.595277',8,14,'media/recipe_images/paneer-butter-masala_VZht9lw.webp');
